 Educational Background



MBA 
Class of 1999 


Harvard University - Harvard Business School

                  Harvard Business School (HBS) is the graduate business school of Harvard University in Boston, Massachusetts, United States. The school offers a large full-time MBA program, doctoral programs, and many executive education programs. It owns Harvard Business School Publishing, which publishes business books, leadership articles, online management tools for corporate learning, case studies, and the monthly Harvard Business Review.                




BBA Finance 
Class of 1994 


The University of Texas at Austin

                  The University of Texas at Austin is one of the largest public universities in the United States and is the largest institution of The University of Texas System. Founded in 1883, the university has grown from a single building, eight teachers, two departments and 221 students to a 350-acre main campus with 17 colleges and schools, about 24,000 faculty and staff, and more than 50,000 students.                





 Career History



Senior Vice President

                                    2010 - ?                


Sarofim Trust Co.






Senior Vice President

                                    2010 - ?                


Sarofim Advisors Group, Inc.


                  Sarofim Advisors Group, Inc., a subsidiary of The Sarofim Group, Inc., is a company headquartered in Houston, TX. The firm provides investment advice.                




Team Member

                                    Tenure Unconfirmed                


Wasserstein Perella & Co.


                  Wasserstein Perella is a boutique investment bank. It provides investment banking and financial services worldwide.


The company advices clients on matters of corporate strategy, mergers and acquisitions, divestitures, and restructurings and corporate finance; engages in specialized research, underwriting, sales, and trading of debt and equity securities; and manages investment funds and products that seek risk-adjusted returns to investors. Wasserstein Perella also provides strategic advice and services for corporations and investors.


Having strategic alliance with The Nomura Securities, Wasserstein Perella has additional offices in London, Paris, Frankfurt, Tokyo, Boston, Chicago, Dallas, Houston, Los Angeles, and San Francisco.


Wasserstein Perella was founded in 1988 and is based in New York, United States.                




Senior Vice President

                                    2010 - 2016                


Sarofim International Management Co.


                  Sarofim International Management Co. manages separate portfolios for institutions and individuals on an account-by-account basis, taking into consideration each client’s financial resources, investment objectives, and risk tolelrance. The firm addresses individual requirements for such items as current income, cash flow, and taxes. Their investment strategies include: Large-Cap Equity. Global Equity, Core Fixed Income and Balanced. The firm's Large-Cap Equity strategy focuses on US-traded common stocks with large market-caps and high daily trading volumes. ADRs, preferred stocks, and foreign stocks may also be based on client guidelines. Sarofim invests in the stocks of high quality, financially sound industry leaders that have an expanding global presence. They maintain a longer-term investment approach of at least 3-5 years, which generally results in low portfolio turnover and is typically tax efficient for taxable investors. The strategy does not use derivatives, options, short-selling, leverage, or IPOs. Sarofim does not attempt to time the market.Sarofim's Global Equity Product is suitable for institutions and individuals seeking greater international equity exposure. While the investment approach is similar to that of their Large-Cap Equity Product, the Global Equity Product has a larger concentration in foreign-based companies and may include shares that are not traded on domestic exchanges.Sarofim also offers a Core Fixed Income Product, which is available to both institutions and individuals. The strategy emphasizes risk-averse management, current income and low cash reserves. Portfolio holdings may include US Treasury securities, US government agency securities, high quality corporate bonds, high quality commercial paper, and shares of money market funds. Sarofim selects specific sectors and securities that they believe offer the best combination of quality, liquidity, income generation, and relative value consistent with their risk parameters. Foreign government and foreign corporate bonds are generally not part of this strategy.Sarofim also constructs balanced portfolios for institutional and individual clients. These portfolios combine the firm’s equity and fixed income strategies in proportions tailored to client requirements.                




Portfolio Manager

                                    2000 - 2015                


Fayez Sarofim & Co.


                  Fayez Sarofim & Co. manages investment portfolios for a wide range of clients — pension plans, foundations, endowments, and individuals. For over five decades since our founding in 1958, we have focused exclusively on investment management. Our firm is an independent entity owned and managed by its founder, Fayez Sarofim, and a team of 21 investment professionals. As of June 29, 2012, our firm had $26 billion in assets under management.                




Investment Banker

                                    Prior                


Simmons & Company International


                  Founded in 1974, Simmons & Company International is an independent investment bank headquartered in Houston, Texas. The firm is a subsidiary of Piper Jaffray & Co. and their ultimate parent is Piper Jaffray Cos. (NYSE: PJC). Simmons & Co. specializes in the entire spectrum of the energy sector. They also provide services related to M&As and divestitures, public offerings, institutional research and sales and trading.                




Investment Banker

                                    Prior                


Wasserstein Perella & Co., Inc.


                  Wasserstein Perella & Co. was an investment bank established by Bruce Wasserstein, Joseph R. Perella, Bill Lambert, and Charles Ward in 1988, former bankers at First Boston Corp., until its eventual sale to Dresdner Bank in 2000 for some $1.4 billion in stock. The private equity business of the investment firm was not included in the sale and was to be sold off to existing Wasserstein shareholders.                




Professional

                                    Prior                


First Reserve Management LP


                  First Reserve Corp. focuses on investments in middle-market energy companies. They seek to identify sectors with an improving outlook in advance of other investors and to establish strategic positions, often in niche markets, before acquisition multiples become excessive.The firm believes diversification of investments across a wide range of energy industry sectors enhances portfolio returns, stabilizes deal flow, enables consistent distributions and reduces risk. First Reserve Corp. invests across a range of segments within the energy industry including oilfield services, energy infrastructure and power and energy reserves.                




Professional

                                    Prior                


Dyer Robertson & Lamme, Inc.


                  DRL is a multi-cap blend manager.                




Intern

                                    Prior                


First Reserve Corp.


                  First Reserve is an investment company that offers private equity investment services to firms in the energy industry. It was founded in 1983 and is based in Connecticut.                





 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ▾




Director

                    2015 - Current                  


Hawkins Capital LP

                    Hawkins Capital provides investment advice to Hawkins Investment Partnership LP (HIP) and HJR Energy Partnership LP (HJR). HIP generally follows a value-oriented investment strategy and employs a fundamental, long-term approach in evaluating securities. HIP typically seeks to achieve a market-related return while maintaining low volatility. HIP’s objective is to provide an enhanced rate of return by investing in a concentrated group of core long positions. HIP also takes short positions when appropriate. HIP may raise cash reserves during periods of unusual market risk. Securities are selected for long-term investment (generally 3 to 5 years), resulting in low portfolio turnover (less than 40% per annum, except in periods of extraordinary market turbulence).HJR typically seeks to purchase energy assets at low or reasonable valuations. The investment process includes fundamental and financial analysis of individual companies, supplemented by a macro overlay of the current global energy environment. HJR’s objective is to provide an enhanced rate of return by investing in equity securities of issuers that are considered to be primarily engaged in energy industries. HJR also takes short positions when appropriate.                  




Member, Executive Committee

                    2000 - 2015                  


Fayez Sarofim & Co.

                    Fayez Sarofim & Co. manages investment portfolios for a wide range of clients — pension plans, foundations, endowments, and individuals. For over five decades since our founding in 1958, we have focused exclusively on investment management. Our firm is an independent entity owned and managed by its founder, Fayez Sarofim, and a team of 21 investment professionals. As of June 29, 2012, our firm had $26 billion in assets under management.                  





